ğŸ“ Right-Aligned Right-Angled Triangle Star Pattern in Java
This Java program prints a right-angled triangle pattern aligned to the right side of the console. 
The pattern is made of asterisks (*) and increases line by line, forming a triangle with its right angle at the bottom-right corner. 
Itâ€™s a great way to practice working with nested loops, spacing logic, and pattern alignment.

import java.util.*;
public class Righttraingle_right {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int n = sc.nextInt();
		for(int i=1;i<=n;i++) {
			for(int j=1;j<=n-i;j++) {
				System.out.print("  ");
			}
			for(int k=1;k<=i;k++) {
				System.out.print("* ");
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
	}

}


Sample Input/Output:
Input:
5
Output:
        * 
      * * 
    * * * 
  * * * * 
* * * * * 

Nested for loops for controlling rows and columns

Conditional space printing to achieve right alignment

Scanner class for user input

Basic formatting and spacing logic
